This command returns a status value for a service. It also includes state information that might be helpful in resolving issues you encounter with the service. Those states are as follows. ACTIVE â The service is running and available for use.

ACTIVATING â The service is starting up, but it is not yet available for use.

DEACTIVATING â The service is in the process of shutting down.

INACTIVE â The service is not running and is not available for use.

